How to Install OP25 For Salt Springers
----------------------------------------------------------------------
This version of the op25 software has a few helper scripts to get Salt Spring Islanders up
and running with the local trunk channels quick and easily. Otherwise this code is exactly
the same as the boatbod fork

Pre-configured Trunk Site
-------------------------
The trunk system frequency this is configured for can be found here https://www.radioreference.com/apps/db/?siteId=36541
The talkgroups enabled for it can be found here: https://www.radioreference.com/apps/db/?sid=7846

1. Install op25 (Same as the main install README)
---------------
sudo apt-get install git
cd ~
git clone https://github.com/boatbod/op25
cd op25
./install.sh

2. Configure op25
-----------------
Install the helper aliases for your bash environment
./install-aliases.sh

Source the aliases into your current shell
. ~/.bashrc

3. Run op25
-----------
op25

You can also navigate to the web UI at http://127.0.0.1:8088
You should also be able to hear conversations in the talk groups
